# The CIA Triad 🔐

---

## 📝 Definition  
The CIA Triad is a model that guides cybersecurity efforts by focusing on three key goals: keeping data secret from unauthorized users (Confidentiality), making sure data stays accurate and trustworthy (Integrity), and ensuring systems and data are available whenever needed (Availability). Balancing these is essential because focusing too much on one can affect the others.

